We are once again in that season of the year when ubiquitous presence of policemen is the order in major cities. Their numbers on the streets can be intimidating, but it is nothing for motorists to worry about. For the average cop, the issue around this time of the year is hardly about particulars but how well he can cajole motorists to make him part with something from their pockets. To this end, they have designed such slogans as ‘Oga, your boys are thirsty.’ Sentry ran into a group of them in Lagos during the week and they greeted with the shout of ‘Daddy, Daddy! We’re here for you o.’